@{
    Layout = "/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

<style>
body {
	color: white;
}
.column-1 {
    float: left;
    padding-top: 40px;
    padding-left: 50px;
}

.column-2 {
    padding-top: 40px;
    padding-bottom: 13px;
    float: left;
    padding-left: 10px;

}

.left {
    width: 30%;
}

.right {
    width: 70%;
}

.row {
    margin-right: 15px;
}
/* Clear floats after the columns */
.row:after {
    content: "";
    display: table;
    clear: both;
    width: 90%;
}

.ratings {
    border: 1px solid white;
    height: 120px;
    width: 95%;
	padding-bottom: 30px;
}

.col-sm-4 {
    height: inherit;
}

.all-h1 {
    text-align: center;
	padding-top: 20px;
}

.h3-grading {
	padding-bottom: 16px;
}

.p-text {
	margin: 0  0  20px;
}

.lg-text {
    padding-top: 18px;
}

.sm-text {
    padding-top: 30px;
}

.diamond {
    background: #b9f2ff;
}

.gold {

	background: #FFDF00;
}

.silver {
	background: #C0C0C0; 
}

.bronze {
	background: #CD7F32
}
</style>

<div class="row">
  <div class="column-1 left">
    <h3 class="h3-grading">TCG Shop rating</h3>
    <p class="p-text">All cards sold in the TCG Shop have a 
		<br>rating from 1 to 10, this has been done
		<br>to help customers of TCG-Shop
		<br>Understand the state of the card.</p>
		
		<p class="p-text">The customer can decide based on the 
		<br>state of the card whether he wants to buy
		<br>the card or not.</p>
		
		<p class="p-text">By doing this we want to prevent
		<br>customers from returning their card after
		<br>they have purchased it, because of
		<br>the state of the card.</p>
		
		<p class="p-text">Rating:
		<br>10: Diamond
		<br>7-9: Gold
	    <br>4-6: Silver
		<br>1-3: Bronze</p>
  </div>

  <div class="column-2 right">
  		
    	<div class="row ratings">
    		<div class="col-sm-4 diamond">
    			<h1 class="all-h1">Diamond</h1>
    		</div>
    		<div class="col-sm-8">
    			<p class="lg-text">The card is in perfect condition: no excuses,
    			<br>This means, that the front is in perfect condition,
    			<br>there are no scratches on the surface, and the surface
    			<br>is perfectly clean.</p>
    		</div>
    	</div>

    	<br>
    	

    	<div class="row ratings">
    		<div class="col-sm-4 gold">
    			<h1 class="all-h1">Gold</h1>
    		</div>
    		<div class="col-sm-8">	
    			<p class="sm-text">The card look like it was used for a few games.
    			<br>The card can have small white spots but they must be
    			<br>very few and very small.</p>	
    		</div>
    	</div>

    	<br>
    	

    	<div class="row ratings">
    		<div class="col-sm-4 silver">
    			<h1 class="all-h1">Silver</h1>
    		</div>
    		<div class="col-sm-8">	
    			<p class="sm-text">The card usually have a couple of white spots at the corners
 		   		<br>or around the border. The surface may have minor scratches,
    			<br>that are visible upon closer inspection.</p>
    		</div>
    	</div>

    	<br>
    	

    	<div class="row ratings">
    		<div class="col-sm-4 bronze">
    			<h1 class="all-h1">Bronze</h1>
    		</div>
    		<div class="col-sm-8">	
    			<p class="lg-text">The card usually show strong wear around the card,
    			<br>The edges and corners have many white spots, the surface
    			<br>usually has scratches and the card usually has accumulated
    			<br>some dirt on its surface.</p>
    		</div>
    	</div>

  </div>

</div>

